fields.name: executeInBrowser
fields.description: When enabling the agent to view or enter data, whether to open the URL in an embedded or external browser window. True: External — open a browser window. False: Embedded — do not open a browser window, which is the desired action when using the On Call disposition triggers.

fields.name: name
fields.description: Name of the connector.

fields.name: postConstants
fields.description: When using the POST method, constant parameters to pass in the URL.

fields.name: postMethod
fields.description: Whether the HTTP request type is POST or GET. True: HTTP POST. False: HTTP GET.

fields.name: postVariables
fields.description: When using the POST method, variable parameters to pass in the URL.

fields.name: startPageText
fields.description: When using the POST method, enables the administrator to enter text to be displayed in the browser (or agent Browser tab) while waiting for the completion of the connector.

fields.name: trigger
fields.description: Available trigger during a call when the request is sent.

fields.name: triggerDispositions
fields.description: When the trigger is OnCallDispositioned, specifies the trigger dispositions.

fields.name: url
fields.description: URL of the external Web site.

fields.name: variables
fields.description: When using the POST method, connectors can include worksheet data as parameter values. The variable placeholder values are surrounded by @ signs. For example, the parameter ANI has the value @Call.ANI@
